in python calculate the average and standard deviation of a list of numbers
import numpy as np 
  
list_of_numbers = [2,4,6,8]   
mean = np.mean(list_of_numbers)    
std_dev = np.std(list_of_numbers)     
print("Average of the list is:", mean)      
print("Standard deviation of the list is:", std_dev)
